  "prompt": "How do I sign up for Quora without Facebook?",
  "response": "You can sign up for Quora without using Facebook. Here's how:\n\n1.  **Go to the Quora Website:** Open your web browser and go to [www.quora.com](https://www.quora.com).\n\n2.  **Look for Sign-Up Options:** You should see options to sign up with:\n    *   Google\n    *   Email\n\n3.  **Choose Email:** Select the option to sign up **using your email address.**\n\n4.  **Fill Out the Form:**  You'll likely be prompted to enter:\n    *   Your name (first and last)\n    *   Your email address\n    *   A password\n\n5.  **Verify Your Email:** After submitting the form, Quora will send a verification email to the address you provided.  Go to your email inbox and click the link in the email to verify your account.\n\n6.  **Choose Topics (Optional, but Recommended):** Quora will likely ask you to select topics you're interested in. This helps Quora personalize your feed and show you relevant content. You can skip this step initially, but it's recommended to do it to get the best experience.\n\nThat's it! You should now have a Quora account created without using Facebook.",
